Attributes (self vs local variables)
❌ WRONG CODE (Local Variable Used Instead of Instance Variable)
class Student {

    int marks;   // instance variable

    void setMarks(int marks) {
        marks = marks;   // ❌ local variable assigned to itself
    }

    void display() {
        System.out.println("Marks = " + marks);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();
        s.setMarks(90);
        s.display();   // Output: Marks = 0
    }
}

✅ RIGHT CODE (Instance Variable Correctly Used)
class Student {

    int marks;   // instance variable

    void setMarks(int marks) {
        this.marks = marks;   // ✅ correct assignment
    }

    void display() {
        System.out.println("Marks = " + marks);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();
        s.setMarks(90);
        s.display();   // Output: Marks = 90
    }
}

2. Question
The following Java code is not working as expected. Identify the mistake and fix it.
❌ WRONG CODE
class Rectangle {

    int length;
    int breadth;

    void setDimensions(int length, int breadth) {
        length = length;     // ❌ local variables
        breadth = breadth;   // ❌ local variables
    }

    int area() {
        return length * breadth;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Rectangle r = new Rectangle();
        r.setDimensions(5, 4);
        System.out.println(r.area());   // Output: 0
    }
}
✅ RIGHT CODE (Fixed)
class Rectangle {

    int length;
    int breadth;

    void setDimensions(int length, int breadth) {
        this.length = length;     // ✅ instance variable
        this.breadth = breadth;   // ✅ instance variable
    }

    int area() {
        return length * breadth;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Rectangle r = new Rectangle();
        r.setDimensions(5, 4);
        System.out.println(r.area());   // Output: 20
    }
}
One-Line Explanation
Method parameters shadow instance variables; this is required to assign values to object attributes.
